caption: Tried this spot already with a friend and I am addicted ever since. I loved the great ambience and yummy food and drinks. 5 stars.
I had a wonderful experience at this place. We liked the amazing environment and the menu. The staff are super friendly. I am happy we finally decided to eat here.

I would come here even if they only served chips/salsa and margaritas. Seriously, they're that good. Atmosphere is super casual and family friendly and tex-mex dishes are on point. Service is always attentive and staff are very friendly.
It's definitely great for families but honestly the food was nothing special and the lack of diversity in the menu was quite disappointing.
Love the margaritas and fajitas. Also great fresh veggie sides - spinach, okra, homemade cole slaw. Once they get back to full menu.

At the first moment  you arrive in that place  they give you an agreeable feeling. Very hospitable hosts, it is a lovely place to to go out with friends and colleagues or with your date. very good  cuisine, experienced  chef, honest  cost and professional  service. Highly recommended.

Outstanding Just walked this neighborhood for chicken enchiladas and found them at Lobo's on Court Street Then walked as fast as I could to get home🤣☺💋💕💓💞 Service was quick and now that I have eaten it was so delicious and really satisfied that roar in my stomach 🤣 Thank you "Lobo"
My top place for tasty texmex. prices were fair. ambience reminds me of colorado springs area.
TexMex, yeah, awesome. food was so delish. the staff was helpful and kind. the place has a cool feel to it. like a restaurant in washington i liked.
Delicious. Love the queso.
My preferred location for tasty TexMex. i love going here. i can see why they have a lot of positive reviews.
Outstanding location for tasty texmex. I was so stuffed. Service is typically great. Bring your hunger - portions are filling.
My fav place for tasty TexMex. Do yourself a favor and give this place a try. The bill was decent. Menu is like a cafe in Indianapolis I liked.
TexMex, so tasty. Super place to meet and chat with coworkers. The bill was fair I would say. Kinda of like a place in Houston that I enjoyed.
Great Mexican food with the perfect pricing.

Maybe it's just nostalgia, but Lobo is one of the best Tex-Mex restaurants I've ever been to. The service is great, the food is delicious, and the atmosphere is just right. It isn't fancy or mind-blowing, but if you're looking for a casual place to have dinner with friends or family, this is the place to go.
Great mexican food and drinks. The staff is very attentive and friendly. I will be back!
Really liked this spot.  Great margaritas.
It was better than expected. I'm not crazy with mexican food but this was really tasty.
Great Mexican Food
Great place to grab a margarita after work
The food was not prepared properly
Delicious shrimp tacos and chicken fajita tacos. I also enjoyed the rice and beans. Family atmosphere.
I've had great meals here before but went in one morning for a brunch and was very unsatisfied. Stick to the Lunch/Dinner menu. Bacon was overcooked, hard as hell. Potatoes bland. Bore toast
Great place for TexMex! In the summer, the patio is the best seat in the house.
Fries took forever to come out, even after multiple reminders. An order was wrong, though the food was pretty good.
Fernando is a great server and is a great bartender and he makes the best cherry lemonades and he is very responsible and he is hardworking and has been the best working person there 😁😁😊😊☺️☺️
The food was excellent for the price and the service was great.
This is actual TexMex. So many "TexMex" places do Queso so wrong, this place does it right. Great spot.

The best Tex Mex I’ve ever had. Cash only but absolutely worth it. I used to live down the block and regret not going there as often as possible. I often go back because in addition to the food they make awesome drinks. Possibly best chips and salsa I’ve ever had. Treat yourself to this amazing spot in one of the best parts of Brooklyn.
our waiter was a really cool dude. also they have free chips and salsa
Great atmosphere. Great tacos. Great service. 5 out of 5 will go back again. Especially for that bartender!
Great food.  Great prices.  Good for families and groups.
Good Mexican food and the drinks on point.
Yeah it's cash only but no better Tex-Mex in NYC! The margaritas are perfection! (GET THE QUESO)

Food was mediocre, but would have been acceptable if the staff weren't so amazingly rude and didn't treat us with utter contempt. The combination of below average food and way below average staff means we won't be coming back and would recommend avoiding this place.

Can't say enough good things about this place; there really aren't any other good Tex-Mex places in Brooklyn (this end of Brooklyn, at least).  The place is very spacious (second floor is huge and there's an outdoor garden), the margaritas are delicious, and the food always comes out in huge portions — a welcome relief given that surrounding restaurants charge the same price but give you half the portion.  I usually come in towards the end of the week and hang out at the bar which is really an excellent centerpiece when you walk in: a great, big wooden bar with the Texas longhorn hanging in the middle of it. They have only one TV in the place (at the end of the bar) as far as I know, but the bartenders are nice enough to put on any game you want, so that's a big plus.  It's just a friendly, welcoming place I can't think of any downside to this place. Although, one reviewer said that they were disappointed that the cash-only mandate wasn't stated more specifically upfront and, on that one point, I can commiserate; I was a bit surprised when I first learned that, as well. It COULD be in larger print on the menu or, perhaps, on the door when you walk in, but, hey, not a big deal.
My favorite place ever!!!

Burritos were good, I've had better at a cheaper price. Puting the guacamole in the burritos and not on the plate is better option. The service was courteous and prompt. However, they only take cash no cards. They should have that clearly posted. Otherwise it's good.
Great food, great service!
Very good Mexican food
Great brunch. Super service makes it 5 star plus
TexMex, yeah, excellent.
Been here several times. Good food and great margaritas. Reasonable prices and excellent service. Nice garden out back.
My favorite location for tasty texmex. you won't be disappointed in the menu and service. service is consistently above par. the bill was fair for the quality of food.
Food is outstanding . Will is the best serving drinks, telling jokes or just singing.  Chill con queso is outstanding! Infact everything I had was great. Must check out
I sat next to a gentleman giving a 5 star review the same time I was. I can't say enough about how great the food and atmosphere is here. Will is a fantastic bartender. He knows his stuff!
Tasty burritos and tremendous fajitas. Would def be back
The host was rude and was talking about my family and I. That how you lose business with horrible  Employees bring back your old stuff the people with respect and that cared about the  Customer
Just beat the crowd. Despite the hectic pace service was great and the food came quickly and tasted delicious.
Good food, best queso in the neighborhood.  Cash only
Delicious!
Consistently my favorite tex-mex. Shiner Bock on tap!
Great food and super staff.

Excellent cocktails, but my wife sent back the fish taco because the fish had gone bad. It really soured the experience of a fun atmosphere near the Cobble Hill movie theater. Cash only, by the way, and a longish wait on a Saturday night. My food, a beef burrito, was fine--but a very large portion. Would I come back? Maybe not.
Great margarita, bar food
Huge servings, very tasty, friendly staff.
They have real Tex-Mex queso!!! That statement alone should pack this place
Nice Catfish Tacos and garlic wings. I want to try so many things!

very good food and awesome service!
The brunch was yummy and sides were great! I recommend the gritsand breakfast burrito. Staff was super nice and accomodating.
Ok if you're looking for queso dip in Brooklyn. Watch for angry woman drinking tequila at bar dropping the f-bomb everywhere in a typically *family* environment.
Great place! Great food ! Great people !!
Straight - up Mexican food with good brunch menu

We wandered into Lobo for brunch. Standard brunch with a TexMex flair. The only disappointment came from the biscuits and gravy. These came with a small dollop of gravy on top which tasted mostly canned. I usually expect these swimming in gravy and tasting a little more home made.

My family love this place. Kids love the brunch offerings (in particular the buckwheat chocolate chip pancakes), and there's plenty for the adults (my brunch go to here is the Migas dish). Excellent  value as well (cash only though).
So good
Solid tex mex with a great margarita. Service is fast and very friendly.
Fresh margaritas awesome
Excellent food. Margaritas are great. Just remember it's cash only
I really enjoyed the margarita and also the enchiladas here, also the salsa is excellent

Of all the places I miss from my 11 years in NYC....I miss Lobo the most. Just started working remotely for a company that is in NYC and have had the pleasure to visit regularly again. It is still just amazing. Best Margaritas ever! Nothing compares in or out of this city.
went here for a birthday brunch and the food was suprisingly really good, and the margaritas also

Service 1 star food quality and taste 3.5 stars. They need to get a system together because everything right now is confusing. Cash only... order at the front... figure somehow out that it's self seating... the owner should invest into a food truck instead of a restaurant.

Food was good. I ordered the tacos but i ordered dessert and didn't get it. The skirt steak is great. Hubby ordered it twice. Rice that came with it was sorry. Atmosphere is nice. Drinks not watered down. Nice staff. I went too late.
Mediocre

Staff is not knowledgeable on gluten or gluten free foods
Great price food n drink
Good food. Hot AF. NO AC! No cards!
Some of the best Tex Mex in NYC. Delicious margaritas and great enchiladas. Go see Will, the bartender, on Friday nights.

This was my go to place through highschool. The chips and salsa are incredible, the chocolate chip pancakes are an absolute winner and the virgin margaritas are to die for. A serious sentimental favorite.
Tasty food
One of my fab local places. Food n drinks excellent service...affordable n delicious. Happy hour margaritas yaaaay
The food and service was good. Their wings are really delicious. The reason I give it 4/5 is that their mango margarita does not taste too good.
Great service and delicious food. Order the fried Okra!
Excellent food.  Salsa is very good.  Prices aren't high for NYC
Giant margaritas and queso are super tasty! And a good place for brunch in the courtyard.
My favorite Tex Mex spot! Everything is good. Can't beat the Alamo special and the large margaritas.
Food had no taste, catfish, chicken steak, garlic mash potatoes, garlic Spinach, onions, horrible don't try it, please don't, service was good, we will never, never go there again
Amazing food. Good ambience. Drinks are ok. Good service.
Great salsa, guac, and drinks! Very casual 2 floors. Could use better music 👌

The only Mexican spot in NYC I’ve found that brings you chips and salsa without you asking (for free!). Food was great and service was fast. $15 or so per plate.  Only downside is it’s cash only.  I’ll be back for sure.
Good food. Great hung out place for groups. But very loud.
Happy hour is totally worth it

Nice place for a cozy date. I had the bama, which was delish. Drinks were good as well. They sell margaritas in a giant glass (think texas big). A little bit on the pricey side, my only gripe was they accepted cash only. Restaurants still do that??? Overall, the atmosphere was great.

Worst mexican food I have ever had. Friends and I ordered so many different dishes and not one was satisfactory.  actually the Steak tacos were ok. Guac is weak, quesadillas are filled with Velveta.  I didn't have a margarita but if you drink a few of those, which are supposedly good, then sure, the food might seem fine.

This was the worst version of Mexican food I have ever had. My friends and I ordered a variety of food and these were the results: The chicken tinga tacos is an overwhelming pile of bland chicken. The guac lacked any flavor. The quesadillas were filled with Velveta? And the mac and cheese could have been prepared by a 3 year old. Saving grace is that the staff is pleasant and maybe the steak tacos. But I have no idea why this place is at all popular.

best pressed coffee ever
Great margaritas great food , unlimited home made nachos with amazing salsa....
Great place, has an upstairs, wish the music was better, but the food is good.
Love their pizza
Their knock-off of queso fundido is pretty raunchy, but their wait staff and cocktails were spot on. Worth a second look!
Simple but well executed dishes
They accomodated our large group with ease.
The best margaritas in NYC!

You can't go wrong with Lobo, and it's a shame their park slope place closed.  Chips and salsa are always stellar, especially when paired with the hot queso appetizer.  The chicken fajita sandwich is always big and delicious, though my favorite is the Flank steak entree.

OMG! My 👍 'go to' fave place. I think everyone in my 'circle' of friends and family has been dragged there by me. I started in 1997 when I moved to Brooklyn, and have been going ever since...20 years. I even had a 'major' birthday there. Big kudos to them as restaurants in New York sprout (and wither!) all the time. The food is always great...and generous. The margaritas are rumored to be the best around. I'm the oddball Martini drinker---If my Martini is any indication of the overall drink scrumptious-ness, then the margaritas must be amazing!

First time in this restaurant. It has a very cozy ambient. Waiters don't bother. Today they had the Margarita Happy Hour and it's pretty much the best one's i've had so far. The bartender definitely knows how to mix it up the right way. For plates I ordered The Wolf, Pollo Borracho and chilli with cheese and chips. I thought it would be around 100.00 for this dinner and was way much less than expected plus tip. The food was perfect and it seems the chef was working hard to bring the food with the highest standards possible.  Highly recommended for groups, couples and even family.

I'm giving this place 5 stars because I think it succeeds in what it does. It's a low-priced casual Tex-Mex restaurant. There is better Tex-Mex in the world, but for the neighborhood it's in, it works. The atmosphere is great and sometimes you just need chips and salsa with your meal. Also, they play really good music (according to me), so it's very pleasant to go into a place that doesn't make a huge deal about itself and just strives to be a relaxing place to get some enchiladas and drink a marg. Being from Texas, the food here isn't blowing my mind, but it's good enough and the feel of the place is right.
Solid Mexican. Won't blow your mind or wallet.
Good Mexican and great mezcal. The bartenders are fun. Good spot to hang for a while, eat some good food and have a few cocktails.

(Translated by Google) Very welcoming server and very rich meal. Tex mex restaurant without surprises but does not disappoint.  (Original) Serveur très accueillant et repas très copieux. Restaurant tex mex sans surprise mais qui ne déçoit pas.
Friendly attentive service accompanied by a nice TexMex dinner. Couldn't ask for much more.
Drinks always great, food and atmosphere perfect after a long day... I always get the mango margarita and shrimp chimi. Brunch buckwheat pancakes are tasty
Sat at the bar and had great service, great packed burritos and delicious chips and salsa to start.
My favorite Mexican restaurant. They have the best loaded nachos!!
Reliable tex-mex
Friendly bartenders and first class foods made to order. The Margarita are spot on perfect.
Yummy Mexican food and not too expensive. Loved the hibiscus margarita!
Excellent pulled pork nachos and fresh brewed iced tea, unsweetened. Definitely has the Tex-Mex vibe going on in Brooklyn. Cool chill staff too. We'll be back when we visit Brooklyn for sure.
Good food and Service

Eh, I'm a little disappointed that I was disappointed in this place.  Was really craving queso and, after reading some decent reviews, queso was the first thing I saw on their menu. So, my boyfriend and I gave it a try. The queso was good, not mind-blowing good, but good enough. The salsa had a nice bite to it and the chips were fresh.  But, I ordered the carne guisada tacos. In a normal case, there's a ton of flavor in this dish, but it was majorly lacking. The meat was good and tender but there was just zero flavor. My boyfriend had the pulled pork burrito and said the same - it just needed more flavor and spice.  Went to pay and found out they only accept cash... but they have an ATM upstairs. Of course they do. I get that some places do this, but for a sit down place I expect to see somewhere before ordering that it's cash only. Guess if they told you then they'd lose a lot of business soooo, it is what it is.  All in all, I'm not pressed to come back here but I'm glad I tried it, it was good service and decent queso.
Great place for margaritas!

The food is awesome! Margarita was badddd. I don't know how they won a best margarita award. Has a prebagged chemical sour mix taste to it. Keep marg simple (fresh lime, grand marnier, agave syrup, and good tequila), no more no less. Food was amazing though!
Tex-Mex meets Brooklyn brunch

Not even close to authentic Mexican food.  Low quality beef, pork and chicken.  Sugar and salt in everything.  Even the lime juice in margaritas is fake - at least squeeze fresh lime!  Nobody wants to buy premium tequila only to have it ruined with lime juice from a can!  This is junk food at best.  Probably all ok with kids who haven't figured out whats good for them yet but if you care about what you eat, quality of food etc. avoid this place. PS.. Tacos are horrible - people, you need to cut up that stew meat you call steak into smaller pieces!
Great service and atmosphere

Lovely staff it seems, love the vibe and decor (at least dowstairs), but the chips are poor, the salsa tastes fine but has poor body, and my enchiladas were really not that good: odd taste, and rather mushy.
Cash only. 🏧 available

Tex Mexico is everywhere in the continental United States. But in Brooklyn it takes on a more advanced flavor profile then most other burrito dens.  The flavor of fresh limes cilantro and chili's are complements to the char grilled meats that accompany your dish if you choose.  The smartly laid out fare is easy on the eye and plentiful.  The staff is well tuned to guide you towards a good meal. The drinks will not disappoint either.  Try one of their famous Cadillac to wash down the freshly fried chips brought to every table.
LOBO came to LOBO and the food was great
very comfortable.  excellent menu. if you love eggs, as i do, you'll enjoy their selection.
The drink the person make is not good. Sorry
Food and drinks where great! The staff makes you feel at home with a warm greet as you walk in. Highly recommended!!

The place has nice decor, really cozy. Outside patio area as well, which is a plus. Got greeted by the hostess and bartender as soon as I walked in. Although, the waiters were sitting at a table on their phones half the time. Drinks were given to us right away, Texas Tea was tasty. Appetizer came almost instantly. Chicken quesadilla was great. I order the enchilada and two taco combo. It was good but my chicken tacos had hidden bones in them. The refried beans were very obviously spoiled and smelled rotten. The waitress just believed "I didn't like them". Hopefully no one else ordered them! I would have much rather been offered another side dish, rather than just getting a side plate to "scoop" off the beans myself. And still having rotten remnants on my plate.
I love the Mexican food, they serve it with a spicy taste. Pricing is good and variety is awesome.
Worst nachos I have ever had
Tasty margaritas.
Cash only. Great fajitas.
(Translated by Google) Good beers and cheese!  (Original) Good beers and queso!

Greattttt food. Great drinks. Great people. Loved it here. I love food and this place is it. The drinks were strong and cheap. All I eat was chicken, I got the fried chicken. The gravy was great. Tasted good with mashed potatoes, chicken and greens. Friendly people always making sure we were ok. I'll be back.

Definitely a solid choice for lunch, as I enjoyed my shrimp salad, but I did not like their guacamole at all, and the flavored margaritas were just too sweet for me (I know, it's a preference thing).  For my second margarita, I chose the original, and enjoyed that much more.

Don't Goto this location, Goto the one in park slope. The bartender was VERY rude and a total snob & this location is cash only, not the other one. So if you need some pricy TexMex, just hop on the train a couple stops and hit up their location on 5th Ave.
Good Mexican food with strong drinks.
I enjoyed the quesadilhas. This place could a larger selection of beers. I enjoyed the friendly and comfortable atmosphere.
Great local place for breakfast. Mexican influenced. Bold flavors. Quality cooking and fresh ingredients. Cash only.
Best. Margaritas. In. NYC. Full Stop. Decent Tex-Mex food, friendly bartenders, and outdoor dining on the back patio when the weather is nice. Did I mention the Margaritas? No joke. Best in NYC.
Not sure why this place isn't always packed. Good food, decent prices, good ambience.
An amazing go lace for food an drinks.  Super friendly staff!  I come here two to three times a month.
Huge portions, pretty standard texmex fare. Cash only nonsense.
Best bartenders ever. Love the vibe. Addicted to the food. Perfect spicy margaritas... I think I'll go now!  Delicious brunch, here I come!

Looks divey from the outside but inside is a pleasant dose of Tex Mex kitschiness that fits right in for Brooklyn brunch spots, particularly the 2nd floor which I didn't even know existed. Staple ingredients served up many ways and in good portion. Was able to walk away with leftovers and a happy stomach. Unfortunately didn't get to try the tequila or any of the mixed drinks which seem to be the star of this place but I wouldn't doubt the care the staff puts into making their drinks as their service was albeit a bit slow since we came near closing time but very friendly. Just be warned, it's a CASH ONLY place.
Great food, convenient location(s), awesome staff and management. Would highly recommend ordering The Wolf!!! True Tex-Mex queso smothered all around!!!
Great food and good prices.
Best texmex in Brooklyn. Reasonably priced. Great flavor.  Nice staff.
Had a good time there but food was just so-so. There are so many insane options within one block - you can probably find something very similar at the same price but with a better menu
Great Tex-Mex, not Mexican, restaurant in the heart of Cobble Hill with delicious fresh juice margaritas. Get the Sangre de Lobo!

Was really disappointed by the quality of the ground beef, and my enchilada was so overcooked it fell apart when I ate it, and not in a good way. Wish I had gone to Taco Bell. The margarita was great. Service was also disappointing, saw 2 different servers throughout our night, one was phased and stopped checking in with us right around when we were ready for our check, which then took 15 minutes to get. Felt bad for the server that was still on, looked like she had tables on the patio, upstairs and then just us in the main dining room. I understand her situation, but if she couldn't handle the whole place, don't know why the other server phased. Will not be back.
"Fun neighborhood bar, good food.  The service is hit or miss.  Nice backyard option - even though the ""yard"" is cement."
Food was not great.  Chicken tacos had bones in them.  Also, it was pretty much empty when we went and service was still extremely slow.
